This article is about a Presidential Memorandum issued by President Donald J. Trump on May 24, 2019. The memorandum delegates certain functions and authorities to the Secretary of the Treasury and the Secretary of State with regards to the Nicaragua Human Rights and Anticorruption Act of 2018. The Secretary of the Treasury is delegated the authority to make determinations and impose sanctions under the Act, while the Secretary of State is delegated the authority to impose specific sanctions under the Act. The memorandum also states that these delegated functions and authorities should be exercised in coordination with other departments and agencies through the National Security Presidential Memorandum-4 process.